At some point between [[7 ABY/Legends|7 ABY]] and [[9 ABY/Legends|9 ABY]],<ref name="Date">{{StoryCite|story=Wanted by Cracken..Update|book=White Wolf Inphobia 53|bformatted=''White Wolf Inphobia'' 53}} is set between the publication of the [[Datafile/Legends|datafile]] ''[[Wanted by Cracken]]'' and the [[Battle of Bilbringi (9 ABY)|death]] of [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]]. In addition, [[Wanted by Cracken (sourcebook)|''Wanted by Cracken'']], which is presented as the [[in-universe]] datafile of the same name, is dated to three [[Standard year/Legends|years]] after the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]]. Since ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' places that battle in [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]] and the [[Death/Legends|death]] of Thrawn in [[9 ABY/Legends|9 ABY]], "Wanted by Cracken..Update" must therefore take place at some point between [[7 ABY/Legends|7 ABY]] and 9 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|ABY]].</ref> [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] [[General/Legends|General]] [[Airen Cracken/Legends|Airen Cracken]] mentioned the '''Kala sector''' in an update to the [[Datafile/Legends|datafile]] ''[[Wanted by Cracken]]'', which served as a compilation of reports on various threats to the New Republic. The [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Victory-class Star Destroyer/Legends|Star Destroyer]] [[Crusader (Victory-class)|''Crusader'']], stationed in the Kala [[Sector/Legends|sector]], was noted in the update as the last location known to that government of the [[clone stormtrooper]] [[Colonel/Legends|colonel]] [[TC-1289]], whose body was believed by the New Republic to host the personality of the [[Death/Legends|deceased]] [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] undercover agent [[Zyix K'zzt]].<ref name="Inphobia">{{StoryCite|story=Wanted by Cracken..Update|book=White Wolf Inphobia 53|bformatted=''White Wolf Inphobia'' 53}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The Kala sector was mentioned in "[[Wanted by Cracken..Update]]," an article written by [[Timothy D. Jacques]] as a supplement for [[West End Games]]' ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]'' and published in the magazine [[White Wolf Inphobia 53|''White Wolf Inphobia'' 53]] in [[1995]]. Since that article was released outside of the [[Lucas Licensing]] process,<ref name="Inphobia" /> it was considered non-[[canon]]ical with respect to the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] continuity.<ref name="UnlicensedStatus">{{UnlicensedStatus}}</ref>

